lenders.name: Main Street Launch (OBDC Small Business Finance)
lenders.loan_because:
Main Street Launch is a nonprofit that provides loans and business development support to new and existing businesses in Oakland, San Francisco, and to veteran-owned businesses across California.

Founded in 1979, Main Street Launch’s mission is to create economic opportunity by empowering entrepreneurs. Through innovative partnerships we provide business owners with capital, education, and relationships that allow them to flourish. Our collaborative approach helps our borrowers create jobs and stimulates economic development in low-to-moderate income communities. Main Street Launch provides loans up to $250,000, and in the last 10 years has funded over 600 loans totaling $41 million.

lenders.name: Milwaukee 7 / MUSIC
lenders.loan_because: The Milwaukee Urban Strategic Investment Corporation (MUSIC) serves the Greater Milwaukee area through catalytic real estate development and regional economic development best practices. Our support for Kiva Zip is to give businesses the financial resources they need to grow, while facilitating business investment that will benefit Milwaukee through new employment opportunities, job retention, and neighborhood stabilization. Providing matching loans at 0% interest to underserved businesses in the area aligns directly with our purpose to combat urban deterioration, poverty, and the loss of population (both individuals and businesses).

lenders.name: MatchLink Institute, Inc.
lenders.loan_because: MatchLink is a 501c3 corporation lending to entrepreneurs in economically distressed areas who have received business training and use the funds to start, purchase, or expand a small business.  Entrepreneurs who participate are asked to complete a short on-line assessment and become lifetime members of MatchLink to qualify for consideration of follow-on funding.
